        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 8:27PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 827 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Springville, or 7 miles east of Paris, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haigler Ridge, Manleyville, Big Sandy, Old Springville, Buchanan,
India, Big Sandy Unit Tennessee National Wildlife Refuge, Osage,
Sunnyside, Van Dyke, Whitlock, Springville, Spring Creek, Porter
Court, Paris Landing State Park, Pine Hill, Routon, Henry, and Paris.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
